WEBVTT

00:01.000 --> 00:05.005
-[THEME SONG PLAYING]

00:12.882 --> 00:15.885
-♪ SOME PEOPLE STAND
IN THE DARKNESS ♪

00:17.017 --> 00:20.585
♪ AFRAID TO STEP
INTO THE LIGHT ♪

00:20.716 --> 00:24.633
♪ SOME PEOPLE NEED
TO HAVE SOMEBODY ♪

00:24.763 --> 00:28.028
♪ WHEN THE EDGE
OF SURRENDER'S IN SIGHT ♪

00:28.158 --> 00:30.769
♪ DON'T YOU WORRY

00:30.900 --> 00:34.034
♪ IT'S GONNA BE ALL RIGHT

00:36.993 --> 00:38.864
♪ 'CAUSE I'M ALWAYS READY

00:38.995 --> 00:42.346
♪ I WON'T LET YOU
OUT OF MY SIGHT ♪

00:45.349 --> 00:49.397
-♪ I'LL BE READY
-♪ I'LL BE THERE

00:49.527 --> 00:53.401
-♪ WHENEVER YOU FEAR
-♪ OH, DON'T YOU FEAR

00:53.531 --> 00:59.537
-♪ I'LL BE READY
-♪ FOREVER AND ALWAYS

01:00.060 --> 01:02.323
♪ I'M ALWAYS HERE ♪

01:20.776 --> 01:22.560
♪ 'CAUSE I'M ALWAYS READY

01:22.691 --> 01:26.086
♪ I WON'T LET YOU
OUT OF MY SIGHT ♪

01:27.783 --> 01:28.827
♪ OH

01:29.654 --> 01:33.615
-♪ I'LL BE READY ♪
-♪ I'LL BE READY

01:33.745 --> 01:37.271
-♪ WHENEVER YOU FEAR
-♪ OH, DON'T YOU FEAR

01:37.401 --> 01:43.320
-♪ I'LL BE READY
-♪ FOREVER AND ALWAYS

01:44.147 --> 01:46.932
♪ I'M ALWAYS HERE

02:22.272 --> 02:23.795
-CROWD:
CHECK IT OUT.

02:25.057 --> 02:26.581
OH MY GOD.

02:31.847 --> 02:32.804
LOOK AT THAT.

02:43.293 --> 02:44.903
-SLADE'S UNREAL!

02:46.209 --> 02:47.384
-I'M GONNA TRY IT.

02:48.385 --> 02:49.952
-YOU'LL KILL YOURSELF.

02:50.474 --> 02:52.563
-I THINK IT'S WORTH IT.
LOOK AT THE WAY
EVERYBODY'S WATCHING HIM.

02:53.347 --> 02:54.957
-LOOK AT THE WAY
HEATHER'S WATCHING HIM.

02:58.308 --> 03:00.571
-IF I MAKE IT,
SHE'LL KNOW WHO I AM.

03:11.365 --> 03:13.105
-OKAY, LET'S PAY UP

03:13.236 --> 03:14.803
BEFORE THE LIFEGUARD
GETS BACK FROM THE SHORE.

03:14.933 --> 03:17.066
-THANKS.
YOU DIDN'T BET ME, DID YOU?

03:17.197 --> 03:19.068
-NO, I JUST WANT YOU
TO SIGN IT.

03:19.199 --> 03:21.070
YOUR AUTOGRAPH
WILL PROBABLY BE WORTH MORE
THAN THE BILL SOMEDAY.

03:21.201 --> 03:22.898
-RIGHT AFTER I WIN
THE O.P. PRO,

03:23.028 --> 03:25.117
WHICH, THANKS TO YOUR FRIENDS,
I CAN NOW AFFORD TO ENTER.

03:25.248 --> 03:26.597
-MAN, WHY DON'T YOU TRY
GETTING A SPONSOR, HUH?

03:26.728 --> 03:28.730
INSTEAD OF GAMBLING
FOR YOUR ENTRY FEE?

03:28.860 --> 03:30.732
-I WASN'T GAMBLING.

03:30.862 --> 03:32.821
IT WAS AN EXHIBITION
AND THAT WAS YOUR PRICE
OF ADMISSION.

03:33.604 --> 03:35.389
-LOOK!

03:35.519 --> 03:37.521
-THERE'S SOME KID OUT THERE!
-GIRL: WHAT'S HE TRYING TO DO?

03:38.479 --> 03:40.785
-HEY, GET AWAY FROM THERE!
DON'T EVEN THINK ABOUT IT.

03:40.916 --> 03:42.222
-[OVERLAPPING CROWD CHATTER]

03:53.624 --> 03:54.799
-HELP!

03:58.716 --> 04:00.675
-[SIREN WAILING]

04:04.244 --> 04:05.114
-DAD!

04:19.868 --> 04:20.781
HELP!

04:21.435 --> 04:22.566
-HOBIE!

04:32.315 --> 04:34.709
-SLADE MADE IT THROUGH.
I THOUGHT I COULD.

04:37.625 --> 04:39.148
-IT'S OKAY.

04:52.335 --> 04:53.684
-DAD, I'M ALL RIGHT.
LET ME GO.

04:53.815 --> 04:55.469
-HOBIE.
-PLEASE, COME ON.

04:55.599 --> 04:58.036
EVERYBODY'S WATCHING.
LET ME WALK IN.

04:59.560 --> 05:01.257
-ALL RIGHT,
WE'LL DEAL WITH THIS LATER.

05:07.785 --> 05:09.309
-THANK GOODNESS
HE'S ALL RIGHT.

05:10.048 --> 05:11.049
-THANK YOU.

05:11.180 --> 05:12.964
-BOY: LOOK OUT, LOOK OUT!

05:13.530 --> 05:14.836
THERE'S NOBODY IN THERE!

05:14.966 --> 05:16.838
-WOMAN: SOMEBODY DO SOMETHING!

05:19.623 --> 05:20.581
-YOU OKAY?

05:20.711 --> 05:22.017
OH!

05:25.063 --> 05:28.066
-OH MY GOD!
THIS IS ALL YOUR FAULT.

05:28.632 --> 05:30.504
-MY FAULT?

05:34.812 --> 05:37.119
-MITCH, I'M SO SORRY.
I DON'T KNOW WHAT HAPPENED.

05:37.249 --> 05:39.600
-SUMMER, WHEN YOU PARK
ON TOP OF A STEEP RIM,

05:39.730 --> 05:41.166
YOU GOTTA PULL
THE PARKING BRAKE.

05:41.297 --> 05:42.777
WE COVER THAT
IN ROOKIE SCHOOL.

05:42.907 --> 05:44.996
-I KNOW, I GUESS
I WAS JUST IN SUCH A HURRY

05:45.127 --> 05:46.737
TO BACK YOU UP,
I FORGOT.

05:46.868 --> 05:48.870
-DON'T FORGET AGAIN.

05:53.831 --> 05:55.529
-LOOK, MITCH,
I TRIED TO STOP HIM, BUT--

05:55.659 --> 05:57.966
-UNFORTUNATELY,
THERE WAS NOBODY THERE
TO STOP YOU.

05:59.010 --> 06:00.360
THESE KIDS
EMULATE YOU, MAN.

06:01.448 --> 06:03.493
THERE'S A RESPONSIBILITY
THAT GOES ALONG WITH THAT.

06:03.624 --> 06:05.843
IF I EVER CATCH YOU SURFING
IN A RESTRICTED AREA AGAIN,

06:05.974 --> 06:08.629
I'LL BAN YOU FROM EVERY BEACH
IN L.A. COUNTY. YOU GOT THAT?

06:14.069 --> 06:15.984
-YEAH, I'M UNDER THE PIER
AT TOWER ONE.

06:16.114 --> 06:17.899
I'M IN THE WATER.
YOU CAN'T MISS ME.

06:25.994 --> 06:28.866
WHAT? DO YOU THINK RULES
APPLY TO EVERYONE BUT YOU?

06:28.997 --> 06:31.260
-LOOK, I'M NOT THE ONE
WHO FORGOT TO SET
THE PARKING BRAKE.

06:32.261 --> 06:34.829
-YEAH, I KNOW.
IT'S NOT YOUR FAULT.

06:34.959 --> 06:36.744
IT'S JUST THAT IF YOU HADN'T
BEEN SURFING UNDER THE PIER,

06:36.874 --> 06:38.180
NONE OF THIS
WOULD HAVE HAPPENED.

06:39.137 --> 06:40.965
-LOOK, I'M SURFING
IN THE O.P. PRO
NEXT SATURDAY.

06:41.096 --> 06:42.445
WHY DON'T YOU COME?

06:42.576 --> 06:43.751
MAYBE YOU'LL SEE ME
IN A BETTER LIGHT.

06:43.881 --> 06:46.318
-WELL, I'D HAVE TO CHECK
MY SCHEDULE.

06:46.449 --> 06:49.321
-WELL, IF YOU CAN.
I THINK IT'LL BE WORTH IT.

06:58.374 --> 06:59.636
-BOY: ALL RIGHT, COME ON,
LET'S GO PLAY.

07:02.465 --> 07:04.075
LET ME TELL YOU
WHAT I'M GONNA DO.

07:05.729 --> 07:07.775
LET ME TELL YOU WHAT
I'M GONNA DO.

07:07.905 --> 07:09.254
ON "STREET FIGHTER II," MAN,
I'M GONNA POUND YOU
INTO OBLIVION.

07:10.778 --> 07:12.736
-WHAT ARE YOU DOING
SHOOTING THE PIER?

07:12.867 --> 07:15.130
-HAVEN'T YOU EVER
DONE ANYTHING STUPID
TO IMPRESS A GIRL, DAD?

07:15.260 --> 07:17.567
-YEAH, ONCE OR TWICE.
BUT IT WAS NEVER WORTH IT.

07:17.698 --> 07:19.439
-HEATHER IS DEFINITELY
WORTH IT.

07:19.569 --> 07:21.310
-SHE JUST DOESN'T KNOW
HOBIE'S ALIVE.

07:21.441 --> 07:22.746
-HE ALMOST WASN'T.

07:23.530 --> 07:25.140
HEY LOOK,
I GOTTA GO BACK TO WORK.

07:25.270 --> 07:27.403
STAY OUT OF TROUBLE, HUH?
I WANT YOU HOME BY 6:30.

07:27.534 --> 07:28.839
-CAN I SPEND THE NIGHT
AT LANDON'S?

07:28.970 --> 07:30.841
-ABSOLUTELY NOT.

07:30.972 --> 07:34.454
I WANT YOU HOME, WASHED,
AND READY FOR DINNER AT 6:30.

07:35.498 --> 07:36.673
-COME ON, LET'S GO.

07:36.804 --> 07:39.459
-WHERE?
-WHEREVER THEY'RE GOING.

07:41.548 --> 07:43.637
-COME ON, MAN!
DO IT, DO IT!

07:45.508 --> 07:47.249
-CROWD:
COME ON!
WATCH OUT!

07:48.642 --> 07:49.556
-YEAH!

07:49.686 --> 07:52.167
-[ALL CHEERING]

07:52.297 --> 07:54.517
-ALL RIGHT,
WHO'S THE NEXT LOSER, HUH?

07:55.300 --> 07:56.998
-YOU ARE, TONY BOY.

08:04.875 --> 08:07.661
-LET'S GO IN.
-IT'S A LIQUOR STORE.

08:07.791 --> 08:11.012
-IT'S GOT VIDEO GAMES.
THEY WANT KIDS IN THERE.

08:11.142 --> 08:13.144
-I GOTTA GET HOME.
I'LL SEE YOU TOMORROW, OKAY?

08:13.275 --> 08:15.320
-OKAY.
SEE YOU, LANDON.

08:19.934 --> 08:20.935
-COME ON!

08:21.065 --> 08:22.371
-[ALL CHEERING]

08:34.121 --> 08:36.777
-HEY, NEVER REACH IN
WHEN I'M PLAYING, MAN.

08:41.042 --> 08:42.390
HONEY, WHAT'S WRONG?

08:42.522 --> 08:44.785
-MA, YOU KNOW THAT NOVEL
THAT STARTS,

08:44.915 --> 08:47.439
"IT WAS THE BEST OF TIMES,
IT WAS THE WORST OF TIMES?"

08:47.570 --> 08:50.747
-MM-HMM, YEAH.
I THINK THAT'S THE STORY
OF MY SINGING CAREER.

08:51.574 --> 08:53.924
-WELL, TODAY I MESSED UP
IN FRONT OF MITCH.

08:54.577 --> 08:55.970
AND THEN, LIKE,
A SECOND LATER,

08:56.100 --> 08:58.015
JIMMY SLADE ASKED ME
TO GO OUT WITH HIM.

08:58.146 --> 09:00.931
-WELL, THAT'S TOO BAD,
AND CONGRATULATIONS?

09:01.062 --> 09:02.454
-[BOTH LAUGH]

09:02.585 --> 09:04.195
-EVERY TIME
THERE IS A CUTE GUY AROUND,

09:04.326 --> 09:06.067
I CAN'T EVEN CONCENTRATE.

09:06.197 --> 09:08.548
-WELL HONEY, THAT'S A PROBLEM,
BECAUSE MITCH IS YOUR BOSS.

09:08.678 --> 09:11.072
-NOT MITCH.
I'M TALKING ABOUT JIMMY.

09:11.202 --> 09:13.727
-OH, JIMMY.
OH, JIMMY.

09:13.857 --> 09:15.076
WELL, YEAH.

09:15.206 --> 09:17.557
BUT, YOU KNOW,
MITCH IS PRETTY CUTE.

09:18.296 --> 09:19.776
IS HE SEEING ANYBODY?

09:19.907 --> 09:21.125
-I DON'T KNOW.

09:21.256 --> 09:22.257
-COULD YOU FIND OUT FOR ME?
HUH?

09:22.387 --> 09:23.475
-NO WAY!

09:23.606 --> 09:26.348
-OH, COME ON, WAY.
COME ON.

09:27.001 --> 09:29.438
-MA, HOW COME EVERY TIME
WE HAVE A CONVERSATION
ABOUT ME,

09:29.569 --> 09:30.657
IT ENDS UP
BEING ABOUT YOU?

09:31.788 --> 09:33.094
-OH, HONEY, I'M SORRY.

09:34.008 --> 09:35.966
YOU'RE ABSOLUTELY RIGHT.
I AM SO SORRY.

09:36.097 --> 09:37.533
COME HERE,
LET'S TALK ABOUT YOU.

09:37.664 --> 09:40.057
COME HERE, COME HERE.

09:40.188 --> 09:42.103
ALL RIGHT,
I WANT TO HEAR ALL ABOUT YOU

09:42.233 --> 09:44.540
AND I WANT TO HEAR ABOUT
"THE BEST OF TIMES"

09:44.671 --> 09:46.629
AND YOUR DATE WITH JIMMY.

09:46.760 --> 09:48.588
-OKAY, WELL...
-OKAY.

09:48.718 --> 09:51.199
-HE INVITED ME
TO THIS MAJOR SURF
COMPETITION ON SATURDAY.

09:51.329 --> 09:52.983
-OOH.
-YEAH.

09:53.114 --> 09:54.681
AND SINCE HE'S ONLY SEEN ME
IN MY LIFEGUARDING SUIT,

09:54.811 --> 09:56.465
I THINK I'M GONNA BUY
A NEW BIKINI.

09:56.596 --> 09:59.686
-I SAW A REALLY CUTE ONE
ON THE PIER THIS AFTERNOON.

09:59.816 --> 10:02.166
NOW LET ME SEE.
NOW I'VE GOT
ABOUT HALF AN HOUR

10:02.297 --> 10:04.604
BEFORE MY SHIFT STARTS,
SO WHAT DO YOU SAY?

10:04.734 --> 10:06.997
-WELL, ARE YOU GOING
TO CHANGE YOUR CLOTHES?
-NO.

10:07.607 --> 10:08.999
WHEN I START SINGING
AT THAT CLUB

10:09.130 --> 10:10.479
INSTEAD OF SERVING DRINKS,

10:10.610 --> 10:12.742
HONEY, I'M GOING
TO BUY MYSELF A GOWN.

10:12.873 --> 10:14.962
[LAUGHS]
COME ON, LET'S GO.

10:15.092 --> 10:17.486
-[ALL CHEERING]

10:24.536 --> 10:27.235
-COMPUTER VOICE: YOU WIN!
-YEAH!

10:27.365 --> 10:29.280
-[ALL CHEERING]

10:29.411 --> 10:31.979
-THAT WAS PURE LUCK.
I WANT ANOTHER GAME.

10:32.109 --> 10:34.895
-HEY, END OF THE LINE, BUD.
IT'S MY TURN TO PLAY
THE NEW CHAMP--

10:35.025 --> 10:36.418
-LET GO OF ME, MAN!

10:36.984 --> 10:38.899
-CROWD: HEY, YOU GUYS, COME ON!
-YOU GUYS!

10:39.029 --> 10:41.031
-HEY, HEY!

10:41.162 --> 10:42.642
GUYS, COME ON,
KNOCK IT OFF.

10:42.772 --> 10:44.556
-YOU'RE REALLY GOOD.
-THANKS.

10:45.470 --> 10:47.995
-AREN'T YOU THE KID
WHO TRIED TO SURF
THE PIER TODAY?

10:48.125 --> 10:50.388
-YEAH. I WOULD'VE MADE IT,
BUT I HIT SOME KELP.

10:50.519 --> 10:52.347
I'M HOBIE.
-I'M HEATHER.

10:52.477 --> 10:53.653
-NICE TO MEET YOU.

10:54.305 --> 10:55.742
-NOW GET OUTSIDE
AND COOL OFF!

10:55.872 --> 10:57.004
-HEY!

10:59.876 --> 11:01.225
OKAY, LITTLE CHAMP,

11:01.356 --> 11:03.227
LET'S SEE HOW GOOD
YOU REALLY ARE.

11:08.363 --> 11:09.581
SON OF--

11:10.626 --> 11:11.714
ALL RIGHT, ALL RIGHT,
ALL RIGHT.

11:12.410 --> 11:13.977
ARE YOU READY?
-YEAH.

11:16.632 --> 11:20.680
-[ALL CHEERING]

11:34.955 --> 11:36.652
-MRS. THOMPSON,
THIS IS MITCH BUCHANNON,

11:36.783 --> 11:38.001
HOBIE'S DAD.

11:38.132 --> 11:39.916
I'M FINE,
THANK YOU.

11:40.047 --> 11:41.135
IS HOBIE THERE?

11:42.049 --> 11:44.312
UM, NO, I JUST THOUGHT
HE MIGHT BE THERE

11:44.442 --> 11:46.618
BECAUSE HE WAS WITH LANDON
AT THE BEACH EARLIER.

11:47.532 --> 11:49.709
NO, THAT'S OKAY.
I'M SURE HE'LL TURN UP
EVENTUALLY.

11:50.318 --> 11:51.580
THANK YOU, BYE.

11:54.104 --> 11:55.062
DAMN IT!

11:56.454 --> 11:57.717
WHAT THE--

11:59.501 --> 12:00.720
-HEY, DAD,
SORRY I'M LATE.

12:01.764 --> 12:03.287
I'LL GO WASH UP
FOR DINNER.

12:03.984 --> 12:05.550
-WHOA, ROAD RUNNER!
COME HERE.

12:05.681 --> 12:07.770
WHERE YOU BEEN?
-AT LANDON'S.

12:07.901 --> 12:10.251
I LOST TRACK OF TIME.
SORRY.

12:11.165 --> 12:13.384
-HOBIE, I JUST
CALLED LANDON'S.
YOU WEREN'T THERE.

12:14.472 --> 12:16.431
-I MEANT JASON'S.
I WAS AT JASON'S.

12:18.607 --> 12:19.782
-[SNIFFS]
YOU BEEN DRINKING BEER?

12:20.348 --> 12:23.525
-NO, DAD. HONEST.
-I WANT THE TRUTH.

12:23.655 --> 12:24.787
-DAD, I WASN'T DRINKING BEER.

12:24.918 --> 12:26.049
-WHERE YOU BEEN?

12:27.616 --> 12:28.704
-PLAYING "STREET FIGHTER II."

12:28.835 --> 12:30.619
DAD, I KEPT WINNING.

12:30.750 --> 12:32.577
ALL THESE GUYS
HAD THEIR QUARTERS LINED UP
TO PLAY ME,

12:32.708 --> 12:34.841
AND HEATHER STOOD
RIGHT BEHIND ME WATCHING.

12:34.971 --> 12:36.756
-HEATHER?

12:36.886 --> 12:38.279
OKAY, NOW IT'S BEGINNING
TO MAKE A LITTLE BIT
OF SENSE.

12:38.409 --> 12:41.064
-I BEAT THIS KID NAMED ANDY
NOBODY LIKES.

12:41.761 --> 12:43.545
SO I BECAME
KIND OF LIKE A HERO.

12:44.502 --> 12:46.983
BUT ANDY GOT TICKED OFF
AND THREW THIS BEER CAN
AT US

12:47.505 --> 12:48.768
AND IT SPRAYED EVERYWHERE.

12:48.898 --> 12:49.899
-HOW OLD'S ANDY?

12:50.030 --> 12:51.553
-15, 16.

12:51.683 --> 12:53.120
-AND HE'S DRINKING BEER?

12:53.250 --> 12:54.599
-NO, THE VIDEO GAMES
ARE IN A LIQUOR STORE.

12:56.166 --> 12:57.602
-WHAT?

12:57.733 --> 13:00.170
-DAD, CHILL OUT.
YOU'RE AGING BEFORE MY EYES.

13:00.301 --> 13:03.130
-HOBIE, IF THE VIDEO GAMES
ARE IN A LIQUOR STORE,

13:03.260 --> 13:05.567
YOU ARE FORBIDDEN TO GO
TO THAT LIQUOR STORE
FROM NOW ON.

13:05.697 --> 13:07.961
DO YOU UNDERSTAND?
-DAD, THIS IS NOT FAIR.

13:08.091 --> 13:09.484
ALL THE COOL KIDS
HANG OUT THERE.

13:09.614 --> 13:11.225
-HEY PAL, YOU STRUCK OUT TWICE.
THREE TIMES,

13:11.355 --> 13:13.314
YOU'RE OUT OF CIRCULATION
FOR A WEEK. YOU GOT THAT?

13:13.444 --> 13:15.185
NOW YOU GET UPSTAIRS,
YOU TAKE A SHOWER,
AND YOU COME DOWN,

13:15.316 --> 13:16.534
AND YOU HAVE
YOUR BURNED DINNER.

13:16.665 --> 13:17.840
-I DON'T WANT
ANY BURNED DINNER!

13:17.971 --> 13:19.450
I DON'T WANT ANYTHING
FROM YOU!

14:29.999 --> 14:31.522
-[CHEWS LOUDLY]

14:31.653 --> 14:33.655
-COULD YOU PLEASE CHEW
WITHOUT SMACKING YOUR LIPS?

14:38.094 --> 14:39.313
THAT'S IT! STRIKE THREE!

14:39.443 --> 14:41.054
YOU'RE GROUNDED
FOR THE ENTIRE WEEKEND.

14:41.184 --> 14:43.143
-THAT'S NOT FAIR!
I DIDN'T EVEN
GET A WARNING.

14:43.273 --> 14:45.493
-IT NEVER DOES ANY GOOD
TO ARGUE WITH THE UMP.

14:45.623 --> 14:47.451
-WHY SHOULD YOU BE THE UMP?

14:47.582 --> 14:49.540
-BECAUSE THIS
IS THE HOME FIELD
AND I MAKE THE RULES.

14:49.671 --> 14:51.455
NOW SIT DOWN,
FINISH YOUR CEREAL,

14:51.586 --> 14:53.370
AND THEN GO TO YOUR ROOM
AND CLEAN IT.

15:46.989 --> 15:52.429
-♪ LOOK MY WAY
I'M ON THE PERFECT RIDE ♪

15:55.432 --> 16:00.394
♪ 'BOUT TO BREAK AWAY
NOW IT'S DO OR DIE ♪

16:03.571 --> 16:07.618
♪ NOTHING'S GONNA STOP ME NOW

16:10.752 --> 16:15.235
♪ YEAH I'M GONNA TAKE THIS TOWN

16:16.671 --> 16:20.240
♪ HEY HEY
WATCH ME BABY ♪

16:20.370 --> 16:23.634
♪ I'M THE BEST AROUND'

16:24.809 --> 16:28.248
♪ AT RIDING THE WAVE
SO WATCH ME BABY ♪

16:28.378 --> 16:31.425
♪ TURN THIS UPSIDE DOWN

16:32.426 --> 16:35.603
♪ RIDING THE WAVES TO GOLD

16:37.909 --> 16:40.086
♪ THIS IS GOLD

16:42.827 --> 16:47.267
♪ GONNA LEAN IN
AND GO WITH FLOW ♪

16:50.487 --> 16:55.057
♪ STRAIGHT TO GREATNESS
STAR OF EVERY SHOW ♪

16:58.278 --> 17:02.630
♪ NO WAY I CAN GO TOO FAR

17:06.112 --> 17:10.203
♪ YEAH I'LL BE A SHOOTING STAR

17:12.161 --> 17:15.425
♪ YEAH YEAH YEAH
WATCH ME BABY ♪

17:15.556 --> 17:18.733
♪ I'M THE BEST AROUND'

17:19.386 --> 17:23.172
♪ AT RIDING THE WAVE
WATCH ME BABY ♪

17:23.303 --> 17:26.741
♪ TURN THIS UPSIDE DOWN

17:27.523 --> 17:31.354
♪ RIDING THE WAVES - YEAH
WATCH ME BABY ♪

17:31.485 --> 17:34.401
♪ I'M THE BEST AROUND'

17:35.228 --> 17:39.145
♪ AT RIDING THE WAVE - YEAH
WATCH ME BABY ♪

17:39.275 --> 17:42.365
♪ I'M THE BEST AROUND'

17:43.279 --> 17:46.108
♪ RIDING THE WAVE TO GOLD

17:48.632 --> 17:50.069
♪ TO GOLD

17:52.984 --> 17:57.946
♪ YEAH YEAH
RIDING THE WAVE TO GOLD ♪

18:02.603 --> 18:03.908
-HE IS CUTE.

18:04.039 --> 18:06.128
I WONDER WHO HE IS.

18:06.259 --> 18:09.175
-HIS NAME IS JIMMY SLADE.
HE JUST MOVED HERE
FROM CAMP PENDLETON.

18:09.305 --> 18:12.178
HIS FATHER'S A MARINE.
HE LIVES IN A VAN

18:12.308 --> 18:14.658
AND HE USED THE BEACH HUT
AS HIS ADDRESS

18:14.789 --> 18:17.052
SO THAT HE COULD ENROLL
AT MALIBU BEACH HIGH
NEXT SEMESTER.

18:17.183 --> 18:19.489
-AND HOW DO YOU KNOW
ALL THE DISH ON HIM?

18:19.620 --> 18:21.317
-INFORMATION
IS EVERYTHING.

18:21.448 --> 18:23.145
-THAT'S TRUE.

18:23.276 --> 18:25.930
-HI. EXCUSE ME.
I COULDN'T HELP
OVERHEARING YOU GUYS.

18:26.061 --> 18:27.802
MY NAME'S SUMMER QUINN.

18:27.932 --> 18:29.847
I'M GONNA BE GOING
TO MALIBU BEACH HIGH
THIS FALL.

18:29.978 --> 18:33.024
-I'M TIARA ENGLISH.
THIS IS COURTNEY BREMMER.

18:35.505 --> 18:37.159
-IT'S NICE TO MEET YOU GUYS.

18:38.943 --> 18:41.207
WELL, I BETTER
GO TALK TO JIMMY.
WE HAVE A DATE.

18:41.337 --> 18:42.991
-HE'S GOING OUT WITH YOU?
-YEAH.

18:43.122 --> 18:45.211
SOME INFORMATION
TO ADD TO YOUR FILES.

18:47.778 --> 18:49.824
HEY, YOU WON.
CONGRATULATIONS.

18:50.433 --> 18:52.043
-HEY, SUMMER, YOU MADE IT.

18:52.174 --> 18:54.133
-YEAH, THIS IS
REALLY OVERWHELMING.

18:54.263 --> 18:56.047
I MEAN, WE DON'T HAVE
ANYTHING LIKE THIS
BACK IN PITTSBURGH.

18:56.831 --> 18:58.398
-WELL, I TOLD YOU
IT'D BE WORTH IT.

18:58.528 --> 19:00.269
WELL, HAVE A GREAT TIME.

19:13.108 --> 19:14.805
-I THINK I'D BETTER GO
SEE WHAT'S GOING ON, OKAY?

19:18.157 --> 19:20.811
-LOOKS LIKE YOUR INFORMATION
WASN'T VERY ACCURATE.

19:21.856 --> 19:22.944
-TIARA: BYE.

19:25.120 --> 19:28.167
-HONEY?
-MOM, I AM SO STUPID.

19:28.297 --> 19:29.777
-NO.

19:29.907 --> 19:31.344
-YOU KNOW, I THOUGHT JIMMY
WAS ASKING ME OUT.

19:31.474 --> 19:33.650
IT WAS ONLY TO COME
AND WATCH HIM SURF.

19:34.173 --> 19:37.045
-NOW HONEY, I KNOW
IT SEEMS LIKE THE END
OF THE WORLD RIGHT NOW BUT--

19:37.176 --> 19:39.134
-MOM, IT'S THE END
OF MY LIFE, OKAY?

19:39.265 --> 19:42.093
THOSE GIRLS
ARE THE MOST POPULAR GIRLS
AT MALIBU BEACH HIGH.

19:42.746 --> 19:44.618
I TOTALLY
HUMILIATED MYSELF.

19:44.748 --> 19:47.229
-OKAY, LISTEN,
I'VE GOT A GREAT IDEA.

19:47.360 --> 19:49.449
OKAY? LET'S GO GET
A COUPLE OF HUGE PIECES

19:49.579 --> 19:50.885
OF CHOCOLATE THUNDER CAKE,
HUH?

19:51.015 --> 19:52.800
-CHOCOLATE CAKE
WON'T SOLVE ANYTHING.

19:52.930 --> 19:56.369
-NO, NO, NO,
COTTAGE CHEESE
WON'T SOLVE ANYTHING.

19:56.499 --> 19:59.023
BUT CHOCOLATE THUNDER CAKE?
WHOO. THAT DOES IT ALL.

19:59.154 --> 20:00.764
COME ON.

20:06.770 --> 20:08.294
-WAIT A MINUTE,
DON'T LEAVE YET.

20:08.946 --> 20:10.296
-IT'S MONDAY.
I SERVED OUT MY SENTENCE.

20:10.426 --> 20:11.471
-YEAH, I KNOW YOU DID.

20:12.254 --> 20:13.777
I JUST WANT YOU
TO PROMISE ME SOMETHING.

20:14.387 --> 20:17.477
-WHAT?
-THAT YOU WON'T GO BACK
TO THAT LIQUOR STORE.

20:18.173 --> 20:20.784
-FINE, I WON'T GO BACK.
ARE YOU HAPPY?

20:20.915 --> 20:22.177
-[DOOR SLAMS]

20:22.786 --> 20:24.005
-THRILLED.

20:36.974 --> 20:39.150
-[ALL CHEERING]

20:51.119 --> 20:52.686
-HI.
-HI.

20:53.208 --> 20:54.557
ARE YOU GOING TO PLAY TODAY?

20:54.688 --> 20:57.734
-NO. I, UH--
I HURT MY TRIGGER FINGER.

20:57.865 --> 20:59.432
-REALLY? HOW?

20:59.562 --> 21:02.348
-UH, SURFING.
ANOTHER HARRY WIPEOUT.

21:03.087 --> 21:05.351
-DO YOU WANT ONE?
-MMM, YEAH, SURE.

21:07.396 --> 21:09.224
ANYWAY, I WAS ON MY WAY
TO THE BEACH.

21:09.355 --> 21:10.791
YOU WANT TO COME?

21:10.921 --> 21:13.707
-NAH, I'D RATHER
HANG HERE WITH MY FRIENDS.

21:13.837 --> 21:15.230
SEE YOU AROUND.

21:15.361 --> 21:16.710
-SEE YA.

21:21.410 --> 21:23.238
-[GRUNTING]

21:58.404 --> 22:00.406
-GET ME BACKUP
AT BEACHFRONT LIQUOR
ON THE STRAND!

22:00.536 --> 22:02.190
-[BOYS GRUNTING]

22:02.321 --> 22:03.974
-COME ON!
HERE COME THE COPS!

22:11.417 --> 22:12.853
-HEY, HEY, KNOCK IT OFF!

22:12.983 --> 22:14.202
-DON'T LET THEM SEE YOU.

22:14.855 --> 22:16.335
-ALL RIGHT, ALL RIGHT,
BREAK IT UP.

22:16.465 --> 22:17.901
FUN'S OVER.

22:18.032 --> 22:19.555
FUN'S OVER!
HOLD ON.

22:19.686 --> 22:21.601
-PUNKS!
THEY BROKE MY WINDOW.

22:21.731 --> 22:24.517
-[SIREN WAILING]

22:25.169 --> 22:27.389
-YOU WERE OUT THERE FIRST.
DID YOU SEE WHAT HAPPENED?

22:28.042 --> 22:30.566
-WELL, I--
-WHO STARTED IT?

22:30.697 --> 22:32.873
I WANT TO KNOW
EVERY DETAIL.

22:34.918 --> 22:36.137
-WELL,

22:37.007 --> 22:40.359
FIRST TONY CHOSE ANDY OUT
FOR THROWING A BEER
LAST WEEK.

22:40.489 --> 22:43.405
THEN ANDY SAID
HE WAS MAD 'CAUSE I BEAT HIM
AT "STREET FIGHTER II."

22:44.058 --> 22:45.625
AND THEN THEY BOTH
STARTED THROWING THINGS.

22:45.755 --> 22:47.278
IT WAS OUTRAGEOUS.

22:49.019 --> 22:51.587
-LOOK!
THEY'RE BOTH BEING ARRESTED.

22:51.718 --> 22:53.197
-COME ON, LET'S GO.

22:55.417 --> 22:56.462
-OFFICER:
HEAD.

22:56.592 --> 22:58.028
TAKE IT EASY.
-WATCH IT.

23:43.509 --> 23:44.858
-HEY, LET GO OF ME!

23:44.988 --> 23:46.250
LET GO OF ME!
WHAT DO YOU WANT?

23:47.556 --> 23:50.167
-I HEAR YOU SAW
WHAT WENT DOWN WITH ME
AND THAT SLEAZEBALL TONY.

23:50.298 --> 23:52.343
-NOT REALLY, I DIDN'T.
-YEAH, YOU DID.

23:52.474 --> 23:55.608
YOU SAW IT ALL!
YOU SAW TONY RUN OUT THERE
AND JUMP ME FOR NO REASON.

23:55.738 --> 23:57.653
-BUT I--
-AND WHEN THE COPS
ASK YOU ABOUT IT,

23:57.784 --> 23:59.568
THAT'S WHAT YOU'RE GOING
TO TELL 'EM, RIGHT?

24:00.569 --> 24:02.353
RIGHT?
-BUT I WASN'T SUPPOSED
TO BE THERE.

24:02.484 --> 24:03.833
-BUT YOU WERE THERE.

24:03.964 --> 24:05.487
AND NOW YOU'RE GOING
TO BE MY WITNESS.

24:05.618 --> 24:06.575
OR THE NEXT TIME
YOU PLAY "STREET FIGHTER II,"

24:06.706 --> 24:07.881
IT'LL BE WITH YOUR ELBOW.

25:05.286 --> 25:07.375
-WHO ASKED HER
TO PUT THE BLACK BALL UP?

25:11.988 --> 25:13.903
HEY, WHAT'S THE IDEA
WITH BLACK BALLING US?

25:14.034 --> 25:16.558
-IT'S TIME TO TURN THE WATER
OVER TO THE SWIMMERS.

25:17.211 --> 25:18.908
-WHAT SWIMMERS?
THERE'S NO ONE HERE YET.

25:19.039 --> 25:20.606
-YEAH, WELL,
THEY'LL BE HERE SOON.

25:21.998 --> 25:23.391
-SUMMER, WHAT IS WITH YOU?

25:24.174 --> 25:25.524
-WHAT DO YOU CARE?

25:25.654 --> 25:27.482
-I THOUGHT WE WERE FRIENDS.

25:27.613 --> 25:29.397
-YEAH, WELL, A FRIEND
DOESN'T ASK YOU OUT
ON A DATE

25:29.528 --> 25:31.094
AND THEN
TOTALLY HUMILIATE YOU
IN FRONT OF EVERYONE.

25:31.791 --> 25:33.096
-WHAT ARE YOU TALKING ABOUT?

25:33.227 --> 25:34.620
-THE SURF COMPETITION.
WE HAD A DATE,

25:34.750 --> 25:36.491
AND YOU TOOK OFF
WITH DAISY MAY.

25:37.579 --> 25:39.320
-YOU THOUGHT WHEN I ASKED YOU
TO COME TO THE CONTEST,

25:39.450 --> 25:41.104
IT WAS A DATE?

25:41.670 --> 25:44.499
-OH, AND IS THAT SO FAR FETCHED
THAT YOU WOULD ASK ME OUT
ON A DATE?

25:44.630 --> 25:47.415
-NO, IT'S JUST--
-YOU'RE GETTING SAND
ALL OVER MY TOWEL.

25:47.546 --> 25:48.851
WOULD YOU MIND LEAVING?

26:03.474 --> 26:05.085
-HEY, LITTLE CHAMP.
HOW YOU DOIN'?

26:05.215 --> 26:07.478
I HEAR YOU'VE BEEN TALKING
TO THAT CREEP, ANDY.

26:07.609 --> 26:09.393
AND NOW YOU'RE GOING
TO TELL THE COPS
I JUMPED HIM.

26:09.524 --> 26:11.178
-I'M NOT GOING
TO TELL THE COPS ANYTHING.

26:11.308 --> 26:13.006
I DIDN'T SEE ANYTHING.

26:13.136 --> 26:14.529
-OH, REALLY?

26:14.660 --> 26:15.922
YOU KNOW, HEATHER TOLD ME
YOU SAW IT ALL.

26:16.052 --> 26:17.967
SEE, I NEED YOU
TO BE MY WITNESS.

26:19.186 --> 26:21.014
-YOUR FRIENDS CAN SAY
WHAT HAPPENED.

26:23.712 --> 26:25.061
-THE POLICE WILL BELIEVE YOU.

26:25.714 --> 26:28.108
YOU TELL THEM YOU SAW ANDY
TRYING TO STEAL MY BOARD.

26:28.238 --> 26:30.501
AND WHEN I CAUGHT HIM,
HE ATTACKED ME FIRST.

26:31.067 --> 26:32.939
-WE'RE CLEAR ON THAT?
-YEAH.

26:34.767 --> 26:35.768
-ALL RIGHT.

26:47.823 --> 26:49.564
-CINDY, WOULD YOU DO
ME A FAVOR?
FINISH THIS REPORT

26:49.695 --> 26:51.610
AND GET IT TO
LIEUTENANT HOLDEN? THANKS.
HEY, JIM.

26:52.915 --> 26:53.829
HOBIE?

26:54.656 --> 26:55.614
-HEY, DAD.

26:56.310 --> 26:57.311
-WHAT'S GOING ON?

26:58.094 --> 26:59.182
-JUST WAITING HERE.

27:02.490 --> 27:04.797
HOW'S IT GOING?
-UH, BUSY.

27:04.927 --> 27:07.756
UM, SOMETHING YOU WANT
TO TALK ABOUT?

27:07.887 --> 27:10.063
-NAH, I JUST THOUGHT
I'D WAIT HERE FOR A WHILE.

27:10.933 --> 27:12.239
-SAY, MITCH,
YOU HAVE A MINUTE?

27:12.369 --> 27:13.719
-YEAH, SURE.
-HELLO, HOBIE.

27:13.849 --> 27:15.372
HOW'S IT GOING?
-OKAY.

27:15.503 --> 27:17.070
-GOOD.
GLAD TO HEAR IT.

27:17.200 --> 27:18.549
LISTEN, YOUR PEOPLE
HAVE THEIR EARS TO THE WIND.

27:18.680 --> 27:20.813
HEARD ANY BLUSTER
ABOUT A FIGHT YESTERDAY

27:20.943 --> 27:23.163
OUTSIDE BEACHFRONT LIQUOR?
COUPLE OF TEENAGE BOYS
GOING AT EACH OTHER.

27:23.293 --> 27:25.295
-NO, NO, I HAVEN'T
HEARD A THING.

27:25.426 --> 27:27.863
I'LL ASK AROUND, THOUGH.
WHAT'S THE DEAL?

27:28.385 --> 27:29.735
-WELL, EACH ONE
SAYS THE OTHER STARTED IT.

27:29.865 --> 27:30.866
PARENTS WANT
TO PRESS CHARGES,

27:30.997 --> 27:32.259
THREATENING TO
SUE EACH OTHER,

27:32.389 --> 27:33.608
THREATENING TO
SUE THE LIQUOR STORE

27:33.739 --> 27:35.479
FOR HAVING VIDEO GAMES.
IT'S A MESS.

27:36.350 --> 27:37.612
-YOU KNOW ANYTHING
ABOUT THAT FIGHT?

27:37.743 --> 27:39.788
-YOU MADE ME PROMISE
NOT TO GO THERE.

27:39.919 --> 27:42.835
-HOBIE WAS IN
THAT LIQUOR STORE LAST WEEK
PLAYING VIDEO GAMES.

27:42.965 --> 27:45.098
-HOBIE, YOU KNOW
A COUPLE OF KIDS
NAMED TONY VALENTINO

27:45.228 --> 27:46.273
AND ANDY VAN PELT?

27:47.100 --> 27:48.710
-I DON'T THINK SO.

27:48.841 --> 27:50.451
-WELL, THAT'S GOOD.
YOU STAY AWAY FROM THAT PLACE.

27:50.581 --> 27:51.931
IT'S NOWHERE TO HANG OUT.
LISTEN, YOU HEAR ANYTHING,

27:52.061 --> 27:53.106
LET ME KNOW, HUH?
-YEAH.

27:53.236 --> 27:54.629
-OKAY, SEE YOU GUYS.
-SEE YA.

27:57.110 --> 27:59.460
-YOU SURE
YOU DON'T KNOW ANYTHING
ABOUT THAT FIGHT?

27:59.590 --> 28:02.071
-WHY DOES EVERYONE
THINK I'M SUPPOSED
TO KNOW EVERYTHING?

28:02.202 --> 28:04.247
I WISH YOU'D
JUST ALL LEAVE ME ALONE.

28:04.378 --> 28:05.858
-HOBIE.
-I'LL BE AT THE BEACH!

28:43.678 --> 28:46.507
-♪ I HAD NOTHING TO DO LAST NIGHT

28:47.377 --> 28:49.771
♪ THINKING ABOUT MY LIFE

28:50.380 --> 28:52.861
♪ THINKING ABOUT THE GOOD TIMES ♪

28:52.992 --> 28:54.776
♪ AND HOW WE SURVIVED

28:55.342 --> 28:58.127
♪ IT'S BEEN MANY A YEAR SINCE THEN ♪

28:58.737 --> 29:00.695
♪ BUT I STILL REMEMBER WHEN ♪

29:01.783 --> 29:06.353
♪ HOW I WISH THAT I COULD
GO BACK THERE ONCE AGAIN ♪

29:08.224 --> 29:11.401
♪ I'M LOOKING BACK AND LONGING FOR

29:12.446 --> 29:16.450
♪ DAYS OF SUNSHINE AND OCEAN BREEZES

29:16.580 --> 29:22.282
♪ THOSE MEMORIES REMAIN
DAYS OF SUMMER SUN AND GOLDEN BEACHES ♪

29:22.412 --> 29:27.983
♪ LIVING ON IN A PICTURE FRAME
DAYS OF SUNSHINE AND OCEAN BREEZES ♪

29:28.114 --> 29:31.508
♪ I WILL REMEMBER ALL MY LIFE

29:35.469 --> 29:38.689
♪ NOW I'M LIVING MY LIFE TODAY

29:39.299 --> 29:41.083
♪ TRYIN' TO MAKE IT PAY ♪

29:41.997 --> 29:46.219
♪ HOLDING ON TO MEMORIES OF YESTERDAY ♪

29:48.482 --> 29:51.659
♪ I'M LOOKING BACK AND LONGING FOR

29:52.878 --> 29:56.664
♪ DAYS OF SUNSHINE AND OCEAN BREEZES

29:56.795 --> 30:01.495
♪ THOSE MEMORIES REMAIN
DAYS OF SUMMER SUN AND GOLDEN ♪

30:01.625 --> 30:03.627
-DROP IN ANY OLD TIME.

30:03.758 --> 30:08.067
-♪ LIVING ON IN A PICTURE FRAME
DAYS OF SUNSHINE AND OCEAN BREEZES ♪

30:08.197 --> 30:13.899
♪ I WANNA LIVE THOSE DAYS AGAIN
DAYS OF SUMMER SUN AND GOLDEN BEACHES ♪

30:14.029 --> 30:16.727
♪ I WILL REMEMBER

30:27.695 --> 30:31.307
♪ DAYS OF SUNSHINE AND OCEAN BREEZES

30:31.438 --> 30:37.400
♪ THOSE MEMORIES REMAIN
DAYS OF SUMMER SUN AND GOLDEN BEACHES ♪

30:37.531 --> 30:42.536
♪ LIVING ON IN A PICTURE FRAME
DAYS OF SUNSHINE AND OCEAN BREEZES ♪

30:43.580 --> 30:45.278
-EXCUSE ME, HI.

30:45.844 --> 30:48.194
I KNOW YOU KNOW
THERE'S NO DRINKING
OF ALCOHOL ON THE BEACH.

30:48.324 --> 30:49.804
AND BESIDES,
YOU'RE UNDER AGE.

30:49.935 --> 30:51.240
-OH, NOT ACCORDING TO MY I.D.

30:51.371 --> 30:53.547
-LOOK, JUST PUT
THE TEQUILA AWAY

30:53.677 --> 30:55.244
AND KEEP YOUR PHONY I.D.
IN YOUR WALLET.

30:55.375 --> 30:56.811
-WE WON'T GO IN THE WATER.
-GOOD.

30:56.942 --> 30:58.900
BECAUSE DRUNKS
MAKE LOUSY SWIMMERS.

30:59.031 --> 31:02.208
-AREN'T YOU THE ONE
THAT HAD THAT PHANTOM DATE
WITH SLADE?

31:02.338 --> 31:03.992
-THAT WAS A MISUNDERSTANDING.

31:05.080 --> 31:06.299
DON'T LET THIS BE, OKAY?

31:08.040 --> 31:09.432
TAKE ANOTHER SIP
OF THAT MARGARITA

31:09.563 --> 31:10.869
AND I'M GONNA POUR IT OUT
AND CITE YOU.

31:11.565 --> 31:12.783
-NO, YOU WON'T.

31:14.176 --> 31:17.310
LOOK, YOU ALREADY
MADE A FOOL OF YOURSELF
AT THE SURF COMPETITION.

31:17.440 --> 31:19.965
YOU DON'T WANT
TO DO ANYTHING ELSE
TO MAKE MORE ENEMIES.

31:20.095 --> 31:22.141
SCHOOL CAN BE
A VERY LONELY PLACE

31:22.271 --> 31:23.490
WHEN NO ONE
WILL TALK TO YOU.

31:25.144 --> 31:26.841
YOU DON'T WANT THAT,
DO YOU?

31:27.755 --> 31:29.496
-JUST DON'T GO
IN THE WATER, OKAY?

31:29.626 --> 31:31.019
I DON'T WANT
TO HAVE TO PULL YOU OUT.

31:31.802 --> 31:33.108
-I FORGOT YOUR NAME.

31:34.283 --> 31:35.197
-SUMMER.

31:35.328 --> 31:38.070
-HOW PRECIOUS.
[LAUGHS]

31:38.200 --> 31:39.114
SUMMER.

31:41.203 --> 31:43.379
I LIVE ON THE LARGEST
HORSE RANCH IN MALIBU.

31:43.510 --> 31:45.077
IT HAS A PRIVATE BEACH.

31:46.078 --> 31:48.080
THE DAY YOU HAVE TO
PULL ME OUT OF THE WATER

31:48.210 --> 31:50.604
IS THE DAY
THE OCEAN FREEZES OVER.

31:52.519 --> 31:54.216
COME ON, LET'S GO.

31:58.220 --> 32:00.266
-DON'T GO IN THE WATER.
YOU'RE DRUNK.

32:00.396 --> 32:02.529
-I'VE GOT THESE BOYS
TO LOOK AFTER ME.

32:09.449 --> 32:10.711
-HEATHER'S COMING.

32:10.841 --> 32:12.321
-REALLY?
TELL ME WHEN SHE'S CLOSE.

32:12.452 --> 32:13.932
-NOW.

32:14.671 --> 32:16.586
-SO THEN SLADE SAID
I'M A MUCH BETTER SURFER
THAN HE WAS AT MY AGE.

32:16.717 --> 32:19.024
-HOBIE?
-HEY, HEATHER.

32:19.763 --> 32:21.504
WANT TO BUILD
A SAND CASTLE WITH US?

32:21.635 --> 32:23.985
-NO, THANKS.
TONY WANTS TO SEE YOU.

32:25.160 --> 32:27.032
-I GOTTA GET HOME.

32:27.162 --> 32:28.424
-HE SAID TO MEET HIM
WHERE THE HOMELESS SLEEP
UNDER THE PIER

32:28.555 --> 32:30.122
OR HE'S GOING
TO COME TO MY HOUSE.

32:32.428 --> 32:33.952
AND HE SAID
TO MEET HIM ALONE.

32:53.667 --> 32:55.190
-THIS IS QUINN
IN TOWER 26.

32:55.321 --> 32:56.887
I'VE GOT MULTIPLE VICTIMS
CAUGHT IN A RIPTIDE.

32:57.018 --> 32:58.541
I NEED IMMEDIATE BACKUP.

33:08.812 --> 33:10.423
DON'T TRY TO SWIM IN!

33:10.553 --> 33:11.946
SWIM SIDEWAYS.

33:12.077 --> 33:13.904
SIDEWAYS!

33:14.035 --> 33:15.819
-BOTH:
AH!

33:38.103 --> 33:40.192
-[SIREN WAILING]

33:45.936 --> 33:47.634
-[BOTH COUGHING]

33:54.423 --> 33:55.859
-TAKE THE CAN!

34:01.691 --> 34:04.390
-[SIREN WAILING]

34:10.396 --> 34:11.701
-OH, GOD. OH, GOD.

34:11.831 --> 34:15.574
-[SIREN CONTINUES]

34:24.844 --> 34:26.020
-IT'S ALL RIGHT.
I GOT HER.

34:51.480 --> 34:52.655
-I GOT A PULSE!

34:55.310 --> 34:58.096
-OKAY, OKAY.
SPIT IT OUT, COME ON.

34:58.748 --> 35:00.359
OKAY?
YOU'RE ALL RIGHT.

35:00.489 --> 35:01.447
YOU OKAY?

35:02.970 --> 35:04.363
SHE BEEN DRINKING?

35:04.493 --> 35:07.017
-YEAH. I WARNED HER
NOT TO GO IN THE WATER.

35:07.148 --> 35:08.106
-SHE'S LYING!

35:09.629 --> 35:11.109
-COME ON, YOU ALL HEARD ME,
DIDN'T YOU?

35:12.849 --> 35:16.157
-SHE SAW WE WERE DRINKING
AND SHE DIDN'T EVEN TRY
TO STOP US!

35:16.723 --> 35:18.681
-YOU REALIZE THAT GIRL
JUST SAVED YOUR LIFE,
DON'T YOU?

35:18.812 --> 35:19.682
-IT'S HER JOB!

35:20.901 --> 35:22.424
-LOOK, I KNEW
SHE WAS DRINKING.

35:23.077 --> 35:24.383
I SHOULD HAVE STOPPED HER,
BUT I DIDN'T.

35:24.513 --> 35:26.472
I JUST WARNED HER
NOT TO GO IN THE WATER.

35:26.602 --> 35:28.561
-JUST LIKE
YOU HAD A DATE WITH SLADE?

35:29.562 --> 35:31.520
YOU'RE A LIAR
AND EVERYONE KNOWS IT.

35:32.130 --> 35:33.957
-SLADE:
SHE'S TELLING THE TRUTH.

35:34.088 --> 35:35.829
THE LIFEGUARD WARNED HER
NOT TO GO IN THE WATER.
I HEARD IT.

35:37.091 --> 35:39.137
AND WE DID HAVE A DATE.
I'M THE ONE WHO BLEW IT.

35:41.182 --> 35:43.837
-LOOKS LIKE THE OCEAN
JUST FROZE OVER.

36:20.047 --> 36:21.962
-TONY:
PSST! OVER HERE.

36:22.092 --> 36:23.181
THIS WAY.

36:23.920 --> 36:25.139
-WHERE ARE YOU?

36:35.497 --> 36:37.456
-[PIER CREAKING]

36:41.242 --> 36:43.288
-COME ON, LET'S GO.

36:44.027 --> 36:45.420
OVER HERE.

36:50.860 --> 36:52.862
NOW IT'S TIME FOR YOU
TO MAKE UP YOUR MIND

36:52.993 --> 36:55.474
WHOSE SIDE YOU'RE ON.
-OW!

36:55.604 --> 36:56.736
[GASPS]

37:00.653 --> 37:04.134
-SO WHAT'S IT GONNA BE?
HIM OR ME?

37:10.793 --> 37:12.491
-I'M TELLING YOU, MITCH--

37:12.621 --> 37:14.493
I TALKED TO
THE LIQUOR-STORE OWNER
10 MINUTES AGO.

37:14.623 --> 37:16.451
HOBIE FITS THE DESCRIPTION
OF THE KID WHO WITNESSED
THE FIGHT.

37:16.582 --> 37:18.627
-IF HE WAS THERE,
I SWEAR I'LL GROUND HIM
FOR A YEAR.

37:27.114 --> 37:29.551
LANDON, DO YOU HAVE ANY IDEA
WHERE HOBIE IS?

37:30.900 --> 37:32.815
-MY OLD MAN GAVE ME THIS.

37:32.946 --> 37:34.904
YOU DON'T DO WHAT I SAY,
YOU'RE GOING TO GET WORSE
FROM ME.

37:35.035 --> 37:36.906
-[PIER CREAKING]

37:37.037 --> 37:38.908
-AH! AH!

37:39.561 --> 37:41.346
PAUL, GO GET HIM!

39:03.079 --> 39:06.605
-[SIREN WAILING]

39:09.608 --> 39:10.913
-MITCH:
THERE HE IS.

39:21.924 --> 39:23.056
-I'M BORROWING YOUR TRUCK!

39:23.186 --> 39:24.231
-YOU GOT IT.

39:25.711 --> 39:27.234
-DAD!
-YOU ALL RIGHT?

39:27.365 --> 39:29.192
-DAD, I'M SORRY,
I DISOBEYED YOU.

39:29.323 --> 39:31.456
I WENT TO THE LIQUOR STORE
AFTER YOU TOLD ME NOT TO

39:31.586 --> 39:33.022
AND NOW THOSE GUYS
ARE AFTER ME.

39:33.153 --> 39:34.937
-OKAY.
IT'S OKAY.

39:37.113 --> 39:38.767
HOBIE, I KNOW
YOU SAW THE FIGHT.

39:39.507 --> 39:41.596
EVERYTHING IS GOING TO BE OKAY
IF YOU JUST TELL THE TRUTH.

39:41.727 --> 39:43.642
-THAT'S JUST IT!
I DIDN'T SEE ANYTHING.

39:43.772 --> 39:46.166
I JUST TOLD HEATHER I DID
SO SHE WOULD THINK
I WAS COOL.

39:49.082 --> 39:51.650
-IT'S OKAY, MAN.
IT'S OKAY.

39:56.045 --> 39:58.134
-MOM, DID YOU MAKE
MANY FRIENDS IN HIGH SCHOOL?

39:58.265 --> 39:59.745
-NOT MANY.
-WAS IT AWFUL?

39:59.875 --> 40:01.877
-NO. BUT IT'S NOT
HOW MANY FRIENDS YOU MAKE.

40:02.008 --> 40:03.444
IT'S HOW MANY FRIENDS
YOU KEEP.

40:05.403 --> 40:08.710
-GARNER SAID I HAVE TO
TESTIFY AGAINST ANDY
AND HIS FRIENDS

40:08.841 --> 40:10.451
ABOUT WHAT HAPPENED
UNDER THE PIER.

40:10.582 --> 40:12.279
-HE'S RIGHT.

40:12.410 --> 40:14.499
-ALL BECAUSE
I DIDN'T LISTEN TO YOU.
-RIGHT AGAIN.

40:15.282 --> 40:17.066
-NOW YOU'RE PROBABLY
GOING TO GROUND ME.

40:17.197 --> 40:18.720
YOU ARE BATTING 1,000.

40:19.504 --> 40:20.940
-I DON'T GET IT.

40:21.070 --> 40:23.246
HOW COME WHEN
YOU KNOW SOMETHING IS WRONG,

40:23.377 --> 40:25.335
SOMETIMES YOU STILL
DO IT ANYWAY?

40:25.466 --> 40:27.033
-THAT'S A GOOD QUESTION.

40:27.860 --> 40:29.818
I THINK A LOT OF IT
HAS TO DO WITH PEER PRESSURE.

40:30.776 --> 40:32.430
BEING AFRAID THAT
YOU'RE NOT GOING TO FIT IN.

40:32.560 --> 40:33.779
-SO HOW DO YOU STOP?

40:35.650 --> 40:37.435
-YOU GOTTA ASK YOURSELF
A QUESTION.

40:38.174 --> 40:39.219
"WHAT'S MORE IMPORTANT?

40:39.349 --> 40:41.656
"THAT ALL MY FRIENDS
LIKE ME,

40:42.309 --> 40:43.658
OR I LIKE MYSELF?"

40:44.529 --> 40:46.835
-YEAH, I GUESS FRIENDS
COME AND GO.

40:47.488 --> 40:48.489
BUT YOU'VE GOT TO LIVE
WITH YOURSELF.

40:49.229 --> 40:51.057
-NOT ONLY THAT--
I GOTTA LIVE WITH YOU.

40:51.187 --> 40:52.972
-YEAH, BUT PARENT PRESSURE
IS A LOT WORSE

40:53.102 --> 40:55.061
THAN PEER PRESSURE.
-NO WAY.

40:55.757 --> 40:57.106
BECAUSE WHATEVER YOU DO...

40:59.631 --> 41:00.849
I'LL ALWAYS LOVE YOU.

41:02.198 --> 41:03.025
-I LOVE YOU TOO, DAD.

41:03.156 --> 41:04.070
-GOOD.

41:04.636 --> 41:06.768
'CAUSE THIS IS THE LAST TIME

41:06.899 --> 41:09.945
YOU'RE ALLOWED
TO BOOGIE BOARD FOR A MONTH.

41:10.076 --> 41:12.470
-WAIT, DAD!
DAD, THAT'S NOT FAIR!

41:14.994 --> 41:16.474
HEY!
